CHANGELOG.md:75:- Added depth-2 breath-to-filter end-to-end test coverage (frac-0061): `tests/test_breath_to_filter.py` now ships a `TestBreathToFilterEndToEnd` class that drives the existing public breath-to-filter API (`estimate_breath_rate`, `breath_phase`, `breath_to_filter_params`, `breath_to_visual_params`) through complete synthetic listening paths. The new tests sweep multiple sine-breath BPMs (3, 6, 12) end-to-end through rate estimation, phase extraction, and filter/visual parameter derivation; assert the documented neutral output for flat and empty RMS histories; sweep a phase table (0.0–1.0) to verify cutoff peaks at inhale (0.25) and troughs at exhale (0.75), resonance peaks at extremes (0.0/0.5), and visual scale/brightness mirror the breath wave; check the documented `min(rate/15, 1.0)` mix-saturation curve across rate steps from 0 to 30 BPM; round-trip filter and visual outputs through `json.dumps`; render JSON-safe diagnostics across calm/fast/flat/noisy signal types; verify rate-detection tolerance per BPM, deterministic pipeline output, and a spot-check of the cosine cutoff curve at known phase extremes. `tests/test_breath_to_filter_depth.py` pins the file's fractal depth at >= 2 (now `substantial (no tests)`, 26 real functions versus 24 trivial). Existing breath-to-filter assertions and the production `my-claw/tools/senseweave/breath_to_filter.py` source remain unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (4392 tests, 3 skipped, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green.
CHANGELOG.md:77:- Added depth-2 audio-analysis end-to-end test coverage (frac-0060): `tests/test_audio_analysis.py` now includes `TestAudioAnalysisEndToEnd`, which drives the existing pure `audio_analysis` public API through complete synthetic listening paths. The new tests analyze tonal sine signals through amplitude, autocorrelation pitch, note/key mapping, content classification, and spectral peak extraction; classify deterministic speech-like dynamic material; retain a sparse impulse through click-transient detection and transient classification; derive silence/onset/sustain/release transitions from windowed RMS values; and confirm public outputs can be serialized into JSON-safe diagnostics. `tests/test_audio_analysis_depth.py` pins the file's fractal depth at >= 2 (now `substantial (no tests)`, 21 trivial functions versus 24 real). Existing audio-analysis assertions and `my-claw/tools/audio_analysis.py` behavior remain unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate remain green.
CHANGELOG.md:79:- Added depth-2 artist-identity end-to-end test coverage (frac-0059): `tests/test_artist_identity.py` now ships a `TestArtistIdentityEndToEnd` class that drives the existing public artist-identity surface (`select_mode`, `apply_mode_to_commission`, `next_tonal_choice`, `MODES`, `MODES_BY_NAME`, `HOME_TONAL_MAP`, `VOICE_ROLES`, `SIGNATURE_VOICES`) through looped, table-driven end-to-end methods. The new tests sweep every `ArtistMode` for required commission metadata keys, tempo-band membership across many seeds, voice-count propagation, silence/restraint/harmony field propagation, sampler-density propagation, voice/groove/modal CSV serialization, the `mode_avoid_attention_pullers` string contract, deterministic application across non-zero seeds, input-dict immutability, JSON round-trip safety, and preservation of pre-existing commission keys; verify the entire `HOME_TONAL_MAP` (only `B` is home, `D` and `F#` are the unique distance-1 neighbors, every distance is a non-negative int); walk the documented `select_mode` priority matrix including the inclusive 0.6 STORM threshold, screen-active gating that requires `presence='present'`, equivalent evening/night routing, and a full presence/time/severity/screen sweep that always returns a known mode; sweep `next_tonal_choice` across many seeds for every mode confirming roots stay in `HOME_TONAL_MAP` and scales stay in `mode.preferred_modes`, determinism per (mode, seed), and that modulation-willingness correlates with venturing (SOLITARY <= COMPANION <= STORM); and run the end-to-end `select -> apply -> choose` pipeline across a presence/time/screen matrix with JSON-safe payloads. `tests/test_artist_identity_depth.py` pins the file's fractal depth at >= 2 (now `substantial (no tests)`, real_logic > trivial). Existing artist-identity assertions and the production `my-claw/tools/senseweave/artist_identity.py` source remain unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate remain green.
CHANGELOG.md:81:- Added depth-2 arrangement-engine end-to-end test coverage (frac-0058): `tests/test_arrangement_engine.py` now includes `TestArrangementEngineEndToEnd`, which drives the existing SenseWeave arrangement public surface through complete tracker-form plans, scene timeline contracts, polyphony variant entry counts, active-voice growth and support dropouts, support thinning while preserving primary continuity, register-band validity, automation interpolation, payoff-scene shaping, cadence quieting/practice lift, JSON-safe dataclass rendering, and multi-family shape compatibility. `tests/test_arrangement_engine_depth.py` pins the file's fractal depth at >= 2 (now `substantial (no tests)`, 25 real functions versus 24 trivial). Existing arrangement-engine assertions and production source behavior remain unchanged; startup identity anchors remain green.
CHANGELOG.md:83:- Added depth-2 quota-aware agent selector end-to-end test coverage (frac-0057): `tests/test_agent_selector_quota.py` now ships a new `TestAgentSelectorEndToEnd` class that drives the existing public selector surface (`AgentSelector.select`, `select_pair`, `detect_category`, `record_outcome`, `status_summary`) through looped end-to-end methods. The new tests walk an alternation/rotation cycle across eight selects, round-trip selector state through `state_file` between two `AgentSelector` instances, sweep a category-detection table covering architecture/coding/review/research/testing/devops/netops/writing/routing/narrative_prose, run an Ollama health-recovery cycle (healthy → unhealthy → healthy) against the real `QuotaMonitor`, exercise pair selection across the default provider set, validate that `status_summary` lists every default agent and quota provider with mixed health statuses, confirm `disabled_agents` filtering is per-call rather than persistent across a sequence, sweep headrooms to flip the winner between providers, run `record_outcome` safely without an observatory across many calls, and verify that `select` raises `ValueError` when every available agent is disabled. `tests/test_agent_selector_quota_depth.py` pins the file's fractal depth at >= 2 (now `substantial (no tests)`, real_logic > trivial). Existing `TestAgentSelectorQuota` assertions and `agent_selector` / `quota_monitor` / `ollama_health` source modules remain unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate remain green.
