CHANGELOG.md:119:- Added depth-2 trust manager planning (frac-0038): `promptclaw/coherence/trust.py` now exposes a frozen `TrustEventPlan` plus `trust_event_plans()` returning the canonical `hard_violation`, `soft_violation`, and `compliant_action` plans sourced from `TrustManager.HARD_PENALTY`, `SOFT_PENALTY`, and `COMPLIANT_REWARD`. `TrustManager.apply_event(agent, plan)` is the single mutation path — it validates the counter field against the canonical set, clamps the new score to `[0.0, 1.0]`, increments the named counter, touches the timestamp, and returns the new score. The legacy `apply_hard_violation`, `apply_soft_violation`, and `apply_compliant_action` methods now route through `apply_event` with the canonical plans so existing penalty/reward and clamp behavior is preserved. `apply_event_by_name`, `restricted_agents`, `summarize_agent`, and `fleet_summary` give operator surfaces a JSON-safe report with the configured constants, restriction threshold, alphabetically-ordered per-agent rows, and restricted-agent count. `tests/test_trust_depth.py` pins the canonical plan, apply-event routing, legacy-method delegation, JSON-safe sorted summary, unknown-counter rejection, and fractal depth >= 2; `tests/test_trust.py` remains the regression anchor for existing penalty/reward, clamping, restriction-threshold, and multi-agent isolation behavior.
