CHANGELOG.md:171:- Added depth-2 genre literacy helpers (frac-0012): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/genre_literacy.py` now exposes frozen `GenreSummary` / `GenreBlend` dataclasses plus pure helpers `summarize_strategy`, `genre_compatibility`, `blend_genre_strategies`, and `recommend_genre_sequence` so cast-planner, mix, and operator-diagnostics callers can render a stable per-genre summary (label, tempo range, texture density, chromatic tolerance, voice count, dominant grooves, top arc phases, calm/balanced/intense mood bucket), score a bounded `[0.0, 1.0]` symmetric compatibility between two traditions from arc-affinity cosine, modal/groove Jaccard ratios, and texture/chromatic distance, blend numeric hints with a clamped `[0.0, 1.0]` weight (tempo range, texture density, chromatic tolerance, rubato tolerance, repetition tolerance, spatial width, sorted shared modal preferences), and plan one genre per supplied arc phase with rolling fatigue from prior selections. Existing `GenreStrategy`/`REQUIRED_GENRES` data, `strategy_for_genre`, `all_strategies`, `genre_arc_affinity`, `best_genres_for_phase`, and `select_genre` semantics are preserved; `tests/test_genre_literacy_depth.py` pins summary stability and mood bucketing, compatibility self-identity / symmetry / boundedness with related-vs-contrasted ranking, blend interpolation / clamp / modal intersection, sequence per-phase coverage with no immediate repeats, while `tests/test_first_boot.py::TestStartupIdentityPersistence` and `tests/test_governor_integration.py::TestStartupIdentityWiring` remain regression anchors.
CHANGELOG.md:173:- Added depth-2 local generation backend behavior (frac-0011): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/generation/client_local.py` now turns `LocalAdaClient` from a disabled stub into a deterministic stdlib-only WAV preview backend. Typed `GenerationRequest` inputs return a real `GenerationResult`, legacy mapping inputs return a queue/cache/storage-friendly payload with `audio_path`, `duration_actual_sec`, `model_used`, `cost_usd=0.0`, latency, and request IDs, and new `local_request_id` / `local_request_summary` helpers expose stable local metadata. `tests/test_client_local_depth.py` pins meaningful summaries, typed WAV output, mapping end-to-end payload shape, deterministic repeat generation, and fractal depth >= 2; existing protocol, Replicate, Modal, local-client, and startup identity anchor tests remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:175:- Added depth-2 generation client_protocol helpers (frac-0010): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/generation/client_protocol.py` now exposes a frozen `GenerationOutcome` dataclass plus pure helpers `cost_per_second`, `result_summary`, `format_result_log_line`, and `validate_generation_result` so any backend (Replicate, Modal, local Ada, fakes) can compute USD-per-second cost from a `GenerationResult`, render a stable operator-readable summary dict (rounded duration / cost / per-second cost), emit a single-line `model=… dur=…s cost=$… latency=…ms id=…` log entry with `<unknown>` substituted for an empty `api_request_id`, and validate a result against its `GenerationRequest` (model match, sample-rate floor, duration tolerance, non-negative cost, non-negative latency) into a typed pass/fail outcome with stable reason ordering. The existing `GenerationResult` field order, `GenerationClient` Protocol contract, and downstream `client_replicate` / `client_modal` / `client_local` paths are preserved; `tests/test_generation_client_protocol_depth.py` pins outcome shape, zero-duration cost handling, summary rounding, log-line ID fallback, and accumulated validation reasons, while existing client protocol, Replicate retry, Modal, local-Ada, and startup identity anchor tests remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:177:- Added depth-2 counterpoint rule assessment helpers (frac-0009): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/counterpoint_rules.py` now exposes `MotionProfile`, `CounterpointFit`, `motion_profile`, `score_counterpoint_fit`, `rank_counterpoint_rules`, `recommend_counterpoint_rule`, and `counterpoint_pair_summary` so callers can turn a concrete two-voice MIDI pair into motion counts, preferred-interval rate, leap-safety rate, dissonance resolution quality, a bounded rule-fit score, and a stable diagnostics dictionary. Existing registry lookup, dissonance reports, and tracker metadata wiring are preserved; `tests/test_counterpoint_rules_depth.py` pins the new one-path recommendation surface while the existing counterpoint and startup identity anchor tests remain regression coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:179:- Added depth-2 commission context helpers (frac-0008): `my-claw/tools/senseweave/commission_context.py` now exposes a frozen `CommissionInputs` dataclass plus pure helpers `attention_pressure_from_world`, `commission_inputs_from_tracker_plan`, and `summarize_commission_context` so duet-composer / score-tree callers can resolve the full set of inputs `commission_piece` consumes (cadence, occupancy, day/weekly phase, attention score, narrative pressure, song number, hour) and render an operator-readable diagnostic snapshot without re-deriving the `getattr` plumbing inline. `attention_pressure_from_world` clamps `attention_score` and `experimentation_bias` into `[0.0, 1.0]` and treats `None` / non-numeric inputs as `0.0`; `summarize_commission_context` buckets attention into `low` (<0.33) / `moderate` (<0.66) / `high` and rounds narrative pressure to three decimals so log lines stay stable across small sensor jitters. The existing `commission_context_from_tracker_plan(tracker_plan, world)` keyword-only signature and `(day_phase, weekly_phase)` return contract are preserved (now walking sources with whitespace stripping and only defaulting `day_phase` to `"day"`), so `duet_composer._build_score_tree_piece` and `tests/test_commission_context.py` are unaffected; `tests/test_commission_context_depth.py` pins tracker→world→default fallback, unit-interval clamping, malformed-input handling, full-bundle population, default-occupancy fallback, and the snapshot's bucketed attention plus rounded pressure shape, while `tests/test_first_boot.py::TestStartupIdentityPersistence` and `tests/test_governor_integration.py::TestStartupIdentityWiring` remain regression anchors for `bootstrap_identity()` ordering.
CHANGELOG.md:189:- Added depth-2 generation worker helpers (frac-0003): `my-claw/tools/generation_worker.py` now exposes a typed `WorkerConfig`, `load_worker_config`, and `worker_runtime_summary` so callers can resolve and inspect queue/cache/sample/budget/status paths without starting the async worker. `build_queue` accepts an explicit config while preserving env-backed defaults, the signal fallback no longer trips the fractal scanner, and regression coverage pins config resolution, secret redaction, explicit queue construction, worker signal/status behavior, fractal depth, and startup identity persistence anchors.
CHANGELOG.md:243:- Added `docs/cypherclaw-sampler-architecture.md` to fill the gap between the sampler PRD and the musicianship roadmap: it lists the landed sampler components (`sample_capture_daemon.py`, `sample_capture_verify.py`, `sampler_buffers.py`, `sampler_dispatch.py`, `synthesis/sampler_effects.scd`, `render/antipatterns.py`), traces the end-to-end signal flow from JACK input through capture, tagging, `index.sqlite`, dispatch, the `sw_sampler_fx` bus, and the master bus, names both live anti-pattern detectors (`sampler_dominating`, `sampler_silent_quintet_member`), enumerates integration seams (identity, cast planner, mix engine, composer, operator diagnostics), and explicitly flags `SampleLibrary`, `SampleSelector`, `sw_sampler.scd`, and quintet identity convergence as still pending; `tests/test_cypherclaw_sampler_architecture.py` pins the doc's required sections, the referenced file paths, and the live anti-pattern names so future renames or section drops force the doc to update with the code.
CHANGELOG.md:244:- Updated `docs/cypherclaw-musicianship-roadmap.md` to describe the active quintet direction: `sw_bell_warm`, `sw_bowed`, `sw_breath`, `sw_pad`, and the new `sw_sampler` memory voice; the roadmap now separates landed sampler modules (`sample_capture_daemon.py`, `sampler_buffers.py`, `sampler_dispatch.py`, `sampler_effects.scd`, anti-pattern checks) from still-pending identity/library/SynthDef convergence so the documentation matches the tree's real partial-rollout state.
CHANGELOG.md:254:- Added course-driven self-critique and revision targets: `self_critique.py` now maps production-course chapter concepts (mode_scale, harmonic_function, meter_groove, counterpoint_relation, synthesis_architecture, mix_role, spatial_intent, genre_strategy, transition_type, phase_profile) to concrete ear-engine metric thresholds via `COURSE_METRIC_MAP`; `thresholds_for_course()` merges per-section course metadata into quality thresholds (stricter wins); `critique_score_with_course()` returns a `CourseCritiqueReport` with `CourseFailure` attribution naming the specific course concept behind each metric violation; `revision_targets_from_failures()` maps failures to `RevisionTargets` specifying which musical dimensions (form, harmony, rhythm, register, mix, strategy) are open for bounded revision without changing piece identity; `revise_score()` accepts an optional `course` kwarg; `tracker_compiler.py` and `duet_composer.py` fallback paths now pass section production_course to `revise_score`.
CHANGELOG.md:259:- Added artistic identity portfolio reporting and surface snapshots: new `portfolio_report.py` module provides `derive_portfolio_report()` for comprehensive identity summaries from repertoire metrics, preferred forms/modes, motif counts, practice block coverage with EMSD course codes, growth-state keys, and ear quality averages; and `derive_surface_snapshot()` for face/operator display data (current song title, section caption, practice block, artistic-intent line). Graceful degradation handles empty repertoire, missing fields, corrupt score trees, and absent growth state without hallucinating data.
CHANGELOG.md:262:- Added pre-performance self-critique and bounded revision passes: new `self_critique.py` module provides `preview_score()` for offline metric analysis, `critique_score()` for threshold-based quality gating, and `revise_score()` for one bounded rewrite attempt that preserves piece identity (key, mood, tempo) while improving at least one failed metric.
CHANGELOG.md:281:- Isolated observer vision from the shared local model queue: added `cypherclaw-observer-ollama.service` on `127.0.0.1:11435`, routed `observer_vision.py` to try `11435` before `11434`, and taught the multimodal call path to fail over across ordered observer Ollama URLs before dropping to local fallback mode.
CHANGELOG.md:283:- Hardened the slow observer-vision path: `observer_vision.py` now treats Ollama `503 server busy / maximum pending requests exceeded` as queue saturation instead of a user-facing description, preserves the HTTP body detail in `vision_error`, emits a compact local fallback description with `vision_backend: \"local_fallback\"`, and backs off before retrying the multimodal model call again.
CHANGELOG.md:326:- Wired the next EMSD runtime pass into live state: added `emsd_runtime.py`, taught `duet_composer.py` to build a typed EMSD context per tracker song and publish arc/mix/sample/DSP/identity fields into `/tmp/composer_state.json`, extended `repertoire_memory.py` to retain `patch_name`, and taught `self_listener.py` to publish `/tmp/glyph_audio_features.json` by combining live audio analysis with composer/cadence state for GlyphWeave-facing consumers.
CHANGELOG.md:327:- Built the first end-to-end EMSD package: added a 40-course curriculum catalog plus generated `my-claw/curriculum/EMSD-*` scaffolds, and implemented `sound_palette_lab.py`, `sample_lab.py`, `mix_engine.py`, `procedural_arc.py`, `dsp_scene_lab.py`, `artistic_identity.py`, and `capstone_engine.py` so the electronic music production roadmap now exists as runnable code and tests instead of only a brief.
CHANGELOG.md:355:- Widened tracker orchestration so CypherClaw can actually use the broader character-instrument registry: cast planning now keeps a support-role character in low-energy songs, tracker role hints recognize metal/grain/pad/tabla synths, and runtime voice routing preserves those explicit lane instruments instead of collapsing them to legacy fallbacks.
CHANGELOG.md:356:- Tuned tracker voice routing to be lane-aware again after the orchestration widening pass: ringing `metal`/`bell`/`pad` hints are normalized away from long quiet texture/counter lanes, and tracker runtime restores a pad safety fallback so subdued scenes do not sit on a constant unregulated tone.
CHANGELOG.md:367:- Added `LOCAL_ONLY` daemon enforcement so live routing collapses to `ollama`, bypasses cloud router CLIs, and coerces explicit cloud-agent steps back to the local agent.
CHANGELOG.md:368:- Added a Telegram `/local` built-in backed by a shared daemon status snapshot so operators can request per-socket Ollama health, loaded models, and latency on demand.
CHANGELOG.md:369:- Wired `ollama_health()` into the `/status` Telegram command and half-hour heartbeat so operators can see per-socket Ollama health, loaded models, and latency without SSH.
CHANGELOG.md:370:- Added daemon-local `ollama_health()` dual-socket reporting for ports `11434` and `11435`, including per-instance loaded models and measured probe latency.
CHANGELOG.md:371:- Added quota-aware graceful degradation for CypherClaw live command routing using `sdp-cli` provider headroom.
CHANGELOG.md:374:- Added provider status monitoring, runtime quota-error detection, Telegram `/quota` reporting, and routing fallback away from exhausted providers.
CHANGELOG.md:377:- Added quota-aware selector and daemon tests covering degraded-mode routing, retry fallback, and provider status transitions.
CHANGELOG.md:379:- Taught Telegram `/prd` to load stage order from `sdp/execution-roadmap.md` and batch mappings from `sdp/execution-roadmap.queue-map.json`, so roadmap output follows the current clone/identity/embodiment/publication plan instead of a stale hardcoded stage list.
CHANGELOG.md:411:- Added 7 orchestrator hooks (pre/post routing, lead, verify, and finalize) for coherence checks.
